  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 spec SC-19 (BINDING — this task's reason for existing)">`/analyze` MUST work as a configuration-only follow-on, validating the platform-extension claim per design.md §6.1. Total cost MUST be &lt; 1 day (target ≤ 4 hours per plan.md Phase 3 estimate). Time/cost MUST be tracked from Step 0 start to Step 10 complete and recorded as SC-19 evidence.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §10 gotcha (BINDING)">MUST NOT add a new prompt-bearing Dataverse entity. `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt` IS the JPS prompt primitive. Add ONE new ROW in `sprk_analysisactions` (action code `ANALYZE-DOC@v1`); do NOT store the prompt in a `.txt` file, a config JSON outside Dataverse, or any new entity.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (reuse mandate — prohibited list)">MUST NOT introduce: a parallel orchestrator to `AnalysisOrchestrationService`; a parallel chat agent to `SprkChatAgent`; a parallel widget to `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`; a parallel SSE envelope to the `FieldDelta` variant on `AnalysisChunk`; a parallel slash-command system; a parallel deploy harness to `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1`. Prefer extending/parameterizing existing components over authoring siblings.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (orchestrator reuse — preferred path)">PREFER parameterizing `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012) to accept a playbook-code + action-code parameter so it can drive BOTH Summarize AND Analyze pipelines from a single class. Sibling `SessionAnalyzeOrchestrator` is acceptable ONLY if parameterization surfaces a concrete blocker (e.g., divergent output schema requires divergent SSE field-emission ordering). Decision MUST be recorded in task notes with explicit rationale per R5 §3.1 step 3 ("cite the gap explicitly").</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new feature flags)">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. The `InvokeAnalyzePlaybookTool` registers unconditionally inside the EXISTING capability-gated tool block in `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools`. Kill-switch coverage inherits via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` when Chat capability is disabled. ADR-032 Null-Object patterns are NOT applicable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 + ADR-010 (DI minimalism)">ZERO new top-level `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`. Any new orchestrator (if sibling path chosen) registers inside the EXISTING `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Tool registration site lives inside the factory (no DI registration required per AIPL-053 precedent).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 (R5 §3.5)">All AI orchestration in BFF; agents created exclusively via `SprkChatAgentFactory`; the middleware stack (cost, content safety, telemetry, service routing) MUST wrap tool execution by virtue of using the existing factory. R5 is Zone A here for the BFF tool wrapper; Zone B is N/A (no Insights consumption from `/analyze`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">N/A for the action-row seed (no index document writes). For the runtime tool execution, tenant isolation flows via the orchestrator delegate (already enforced by task 012). Confirm in notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 (R5 §3.2)">N/A — no new feature flags. Confirm in notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 + R5 NFR-07 + CLAUDE.md §10 (publish-size — BINDING per-task)">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed output; report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline (post-task-031). Target ≤ +0.1 MB delta. Escalation threshold: +0.5 MB (signals the "configuration-only" claim is at risk — INVESTIGATE before proceeding). Ceiling: 60 MB compressed (NFR-01). R5 cumulative budget ≤ +1 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-02 + task 017 widget contract">Output schema field paths MUST drive `FieldDelta.Path` SSE events that `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) consumes WITHOUT modification. The widget MUST render `/analyze` output via the same schema-driven mechanism it renders `/summarize` output. If the widget requires ANY modification to render `/analyze` output, the schema-driven claim (SC-19 + NFR-12) is contradicted — record explicitly in task notes and escalate per R5 §6.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-11 (decline-to-find)">Output schema MUST support decline-to-find via the same mechanism task 010 used (preferred: delegation to `DeclineToFindNode` with clean schema; alternative: discriminated branch). Use the SAME decision the Summarize action took (record in notes); deviation requires justification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12 (tool routing discipline)">`InvokeAnalyzePlaybookTool` description text is load-bearing for correct LLM routing. The description MUST scope routing to "analyze files uploaded to the current chat session" and MUST NOT overlap semantically with `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` (task 015) or `insights.query` (task 024). The Summarize-vs-Analyze disambiguation is a UR-01-class risk; mitigate via description discipline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F (test obligation)">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Minimal tests: tool-delegation test, tool-discoverable-in-factory test, slash-command-routing test. Heavier convergence tests are NOT required for the proof point (this is a measurement task, not a depth-of-quality task), but the minimal test surface MUST exist.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (idempotency — BINDING)">Re-running the action-row + playbook-row deploy against an environment that already has the rows MUST be a no-op (skip-on-exists by `sprk_actioncode` + `sprk_name` lookup). Mirrors task 010 + task 011 idempotency pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (measurement discipline — BINDING)">SC-19 is a MEASUREMENT claim. Time/cost tracking is a FIRST-CLASS deliverable, not metadata. Step 0 records start timestamp; Step 10 records end timestamp; total elapsed time MUST appear in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md`. Files modified count + LOC delta + publish-size delta MUST be measured + recorded. A FAILED proof point (cost &gt; 1 day; widget required modification; orchestrator could not be parameterized) is VALID evidence — record honestly.</constraint>
  </constraints>

