      `pwsh scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1 -DefinitionFile src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Playbooks/analyze-for-chat.playbook.json`.
      Capture stdout to `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md`: action-row GUID,
      playbook-row GUID, deploy elapsed time. Idempotency verification:
      re-run the SAME command and confirm skip-on-exists semantics (exit 0; no
      duplicates).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Implement BFF Tool Wrapper (per Step 3 decision)">
      Path A (parameterize): Edit `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs` to accept
      `playbookCode` + `actionCode` arguments on its primary method. Update task
      014 endpoint + task 015 tool callers to pass `'summarize-for-chat@v1'` +
      `'SUM-CHAT@v1'` explicitly (was implicit before). NO new file, NO new DI
      line.

      Path B (sibling): Create
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionAnalyzeOrchestrator.cs`
      delegating to shared streaming infrastructure. Register inside the EXISTING
      `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (one new `AddScoped&lt;SessionAnalyzeOrchestrator&gt;()`
      line — ADR-010 compliant).

      Then (both paths): Create
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/InvokeAnalyzePlaybookTool.cs`
      mirroring task 015's `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool.cs` exactly. Tool
      description text (NFR-12-discipline):

      "Analyze files uploaded to the current chat session via the Analyze
      playbook — produces a structured analysis with summary, key findings,
      risks, and recommendations. Use when the user asks to analyze, review,
      assess, or critique attached session files. Do NOT use for: bare
      summarization requests (use InvokeSummarizePlaybook for that); analytical
      questions about a matter/project/invoice entity (use insights.query for
      that)."

      Wire into `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` adjacent to the
      `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` block (one new capability-gated block;
      AIPU2-063 try/catch error isolation; mirror task 015 Step 5 pattern
      exactly). Add the tool name to the appropriate capability manifest's
