    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor) + Publish-Size Measurement (BINDING per CLAUDE.md §10)">
      Run `code-review` skill against all changed files (Dataverse JSON, BFF
      orchestrator change OR new orchestrator file, tool wrapper class, factory
      extension, slash-command types file, intent-handler change, test files).
      Run `adr-check` skill against the same; verify: ADR-013 (BFF-only AI;
      agent via factory; middleware inherited), ADR-010 (DI minimalism — Path A:
      zero new DI lines; Path B: one new line in EXISTING module), ADR-018 (no
      new feature flag — kill-switch inherits via NullSprkChatAgentFactory),
      ADR-014 (tenant isolation flows via orchestrator delegate — N/A for
      action-row seed itself but confirmed for runtime tool execution), ADR-028
      (no token snapshot — OBO passes through), ADR-029 (publish hygiene — see
      below), ADR-030 (no new PaneEventBus channel — `FieldDelta` events flow
      through existing `workspace.field_delta` event type from task 016).

      Run BFF publish + size check:
      `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`
      Measure compressed output. Record in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md`:
      absolute size + delta vs prior baseline (post-task-031 baseline). Target
      ≤ +0.1 MB. Escalation threshold +0.5 MB — if delta ≥ +0.5 MB, STOP and
      investigate; SC-19 "configuration-only" claim is at risk. CVE scan:
      `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — confirm clean.

      Both quality gates MUST pass before marking task complete. Record gate
      outputs (code-review summary + adr-check verdict + publish size + CVE
      scan output) in evidence notes.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Record END TIMESTAMP + Compute SC-19 Verdict + Document + Complete">
      **RECORD END TIMESTAMP** in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md`:
      `END: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS UTC (Step 10 begin)`. Compute total elapsed
      time = END - START. Record explicitly.

      Compute SC-19 verdict in evidence notes:
      - **FULL PASS** if: total time &lt; 4 hours AND orchestrator Path A taken
        (no parallel orchestrator) AND widget rendered without modification AND
        publish-size delta ≤ +0.1 MB.
      - **PARTIAL PASS** if: total time &lt; 1 day (8 hours) AND ≤ 1 of the three
        non-time constraints was deviated.
      - **FAIL** if: total time ≥ 1 day OR ≥ 2 of the three non-time constraints
        were deviated.

      The verdict + supporting numbers feed directly into task 044 (D3-05
      lessons-learned). Be honest — a PARTIAL or FAIL verdict is valuable
      evidence about R5 architecture maturity, not a stigma.

      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 040 🔲 →
