  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">New row in Spaarke Dev Dataverse `sprk_analysisactions` collection: `sprk_actioncode = 'ANALYZE-DOC@v1'`, `sprk_name = 'Analyze Document for Chat'`. Verified via `az rest` `$filter` query at Step 6 idempotency check.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">New row in Spaarke Dev Dataverse `sprk_analysisplaybooks` collection: playbook name `analyze-for-chat@v1` with one primary LLM-analysis node referencing `actionCode = 'ANALYZE-DOC@v1'`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Action row's `sprk_systemprompt` field contains the JPS-formatted prompt (per Step 4) — NOT a free-text prompt, NOT loaded from a `.txt` file. Output schema (in whichever field task 010's discovery confirmed) is the Step 4 JSON Schema verbatim with required fields `analysisSummary`, `keyFindings`, `risks`, `recommendations`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Deploy uses `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (or its task-010 extension) — NOT a parallel deploy mechanism. Idempotent: re-running deploys without `-Force` is a no-op (skip-on-exists; no duplicates).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Orchestrator path decision recorded in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md` with rationale: Path A (parameterize `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`) PREFERRED; Path B (sibling `SessionAnalyzeOrchestrator`) acceptable only with explicit gap citation per R5 §3.1.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`InvokeAnalyzePlaybookTool` is registered via the EXISTING `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism (no new chat agent, no new tool framework, ZERO new top-level Program.cs lines). Tool function `InvokeAnalyzePlaybookAsync` accepts EXACTLY two parameters: `fileIds: string[]?` and `style: string?` (mirroring task 015 signature for shape consistency).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool description text explicitly scopes routing to Analyze semantics AND explicitly differentiates from `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` (task 015) AND `insights.query` (task 024) per NFR-12. Final description recorded in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">New `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` entry for `/analyze` is added in `slashCommandMenu.types.ts` adjacent to `/summarize`. ConversationPane intent-handler routes `/analyze` to the agent-tool path mirroring task 019's pattern.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke test passes end-to-end on Spaarke Dev: slash-command path (`/analyze` after file upload) AND natural-language path ("analyze the attached documents") both produce structured output rendered progressively in Workspace pane via `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`. Activity span IDs / log traces captured for both paths.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) renders `/analyze` output WITHOUT modification — proving the widget is genuinely schema-driven. If a new renderer was required, the deviation is explicitly recorded in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md` (partial SC-19 credit).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ZERO new feature flags introduced (ADR-018 / R5 §3.2); tool registers unconditionally inside the existing capability-gated block; kill-switch coverage inherits via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory`. Confirmed by `adr-check` pass at Step 9.5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta measured + recorded (per R5 §3.6 + CLAUDE.md §10); target ≤ +0.1 MB; escalation threshold +0.5 MB. Actual delta recorded in `notes/sc-19-proof-point-evidence.md`. R5 cumulative budget ≤ +1 MB still honored.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new HIGH-severity CVE introduced (`dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` clean).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5 (ADR-013, ADR-010, ADR-018, ADR-014, ADR-028, ADR-029, ADR-030 confirmed).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Minimal test surface exists: `InvokeAnalyzePlaybookToolTests.cs` covers tool delegation + tool discoverability in factory (mirroring task 015's test minimum). Heavier convergence tests NOT required for proof-point measurement task.</criterion>
